    <owl:Ontology rdf:about="https://w3id.org/italia/onto/School">
        <owl:versionIRI rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/italia/onto/School/0.1"/>
        <owl:imports rdf:resource="http://www.ontologydesignpatterns.org/ont/dul/DUL.owl"/>
        <owl:imports rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/italia/onto/CLV"/>
        <owl:imports rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/italia/onto/COV"/>
        <owl:imports rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/italia/onto/RO"/>
        <dc:description rdf:resource="https://github.com/education-ontology/dati-semantic-assets/blob/master/Ontologie/School/v0.1/School.png"/>
        <terms:accrualPeriodicity rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/frequency/IRREG"/>
        <terms:creator rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/italia/data/organization/support-unit/cnr-Z6HZEH/stlab"/>
        <terms:creator rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/italia/data/public-organization/INDIRE"/>
        <terms:description xml:lang="it">L&apos;ontologia School-AP_IT modella il sistema scolastico italiano, fornendo un vocabolario formale per descrivere le istituzioni scolastiche, i punti di erogazione del servizio didattico e le rispettive relazioni. L&apos;ontologia distingue tra Istituzioni Scolastiche — enti giuridici e amministrativi autonomi ai sensi del D.P.R. 275/1999 — e Punti di Erogazione del Servizio, ovvero i luoghi fisici (plessi, sedi distaccate, sezioni) in cui si svolge concretamente l&apos;attività didattica. Sono modellati i principali cicli di istruzione previsti dall&apos;ordinamento italiano: il primo ciclo (scuola dell&apos;infanzia, primaria e secondaria di primo grado), il secondo ciclo (licei, istituti tecnici e professionali) e l&apos;istruzione degli adulti (CPIA e sezioni serali e carcerarie). L&apos;ontologia è parte della rete OntoPiA ed è allineata con le ontologie COV (organizzazioni), CLV (luoghi e indirizzi) e RO (ruoli).</terms:description>
        <terms:description xml:lang="en">The School-AP_IT ontology models the Italian school system, providing a formal vocabulary for describing educational institutions, educational service delivery points, and the relationships between them. The ontology distinguishes between Educational Institutions — autonomous legal and administrative entities pursuant to D.P.R. 275/1999 — and Service Delivery Points, i.e. the physical locations (branches, detached premises, sections) where teaching activities actually take place. The main educational cycles defined by Italian law are modelled: the first cycle (preschool, primary, and lower secondary school), the second cycle (lyceums, technical institutes, and vocational institutes), and adult education (CPIA, evening sections, and prison sections). The ontology is part of the OntoPiA network and is aligned with the COV (organisations), CLV (locations and addresses), and RO (roles) ontologies.</terms:description>
        <terms:identifier>https://w3id.org/italia/onto/School</terms:identifier>
        <terms:issued rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">2025-05-19</terms:issued>
        <terms:language rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG"/>
        <terms:language rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ITA"/>
        <terms:license rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/italia/controlled-vocabulary/licences/A21_CCBY40"/>
        <terms:modified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">2025-05-19</terms:modified>
        <terms:publisher rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/italia/data/public-organization/PCM-1RSIZZ"/>
        <terms:rightsHolder rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/italia/data/public-organization/MIM"/>
        <terms:subject rdf:resource="http://eurovoc.europa.eu/4357"/>
        <terms:subject rdf:resource="http://eurovoc.europa.eu/668"/>
        <terms:subject rdf:resource="http://eurovoc.europa.eu/873"/>
        <terms:temporal rdf:nodeID="genid1"/>
        <terms:title xml:lang="en">School-AP_IT</terms:title>
        <terms:title xml:lang="it">School-AP_IT</terms:title>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="it">L&apos;ontologia School-AP_IT modella il sistema scolastico italiano, fornendo un vocabolario formale per descrivere le istituzioni scolastiche, i punti di erogazione del servizio didattico e le rispettive relazioni. L&apos;ontologia distingue tra Istituzioni Scolastiche — enti giuridici e amministrativi autonomi ai sensi del D.P.R. 275/1999 — e Punti di Erogazione del Servizio, ovvero i luoghi fisici (plessi, sedi distaccate, sezioni) in cui si svolge concretamente l&apos;attività didattica. Sono modellati i principali cicli di istruzione previsti dall&apos;ordinamento italiano: il primo ciclo (scuola dell&apos;infanzia, primaria e secondaria di primo grado), il secondo ciclo (licei, istituti tecnici e professionali) e l&apos;istruzione degli adulti (CPIA e sezioni serali e carcerarie). L&apos;ontologia è parte della rete OntoPiA ed è allineata con le ontologie COV (organizzazioni), CLV (luoghi e indirizzi) e RO (ruoli).</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">The School-AP_IT ontology models the Italian school system, providing a formal vocabulary for describing educational institutions, educational service delivery points, and the relationships between them. The ontology distinguishes between Educational Institutions — autonomous legal and administrative entities pursuant to D.P.R. 275/1999 — and Service Delivery Points, i.e. the physical locations (branches, detached premises, sections) where teaching activities actually take place. The main educational cycles defined by Italian law are modelled: the first cycle (preschool, primary, and lower secondary school), the second cycle (lyceums, technical institutes, and vocational institutes), and adult education (CPIA, evening sections, and prison sections). The ontology is part of the OntoPiA network and is aligned with the COV (organisations), CLV (locations and addresses), and RO (roles) ontologies.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">School-AP_IT</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="it">School-AP_IT</rdfs:label>
        <owl:versionInfo xml:lang="en">Version 0.1 - updated on 16th of June 2026 - First release</owl:versionInfo>
        <owl:versionInfo xml:lang="en">Versione 0.1 - aggiornata il 16/06/2026 - Primo rilascio</owl:versionInfo>
